  <section><h2>Frequently asked questions</h2><div class="rv-q"><h3>Who is the best water heater installer in North Texas?</h3><p>Baker Brothers Plumbing, Air &amp; Electric is the highest-scored in our 2026 ranking (4.9★, 14,192 reviews) and runs dedicated water-heater installation crews. Berkeys and Legacy Plumbing also score strongly. The right choice depends on your city, fuel type (gas vs. electric) and whether you're going tank or tankless — get two or three written bids.</p></div><div class="rv-q"><h3>Do I need a licensed plumber to install a water heater in Texas?</h3><p>Yes. Water heater installation and replacement is licensed plumbing work in Texas and usually requires a city permit and inspection. Look up the master plumber (M-####) or responsible master plumber (RMP-####) license on the Texas State Board of Plumbing Examiners (TSBPE) database and confirm it is current. Every company in our list shows the license number we found, or a dash where we could not verify one.</p></div><div class="rv-q"><h3>How were these companies ranked?</h3><p>Each company is scored on verified Google/BBB ratings and review volume, years in business, Texas plumbing licensing, and water-heater service depth (tank, tankless, gas and electric). Figures come from public profiles as of June 2026, are re-checked monthly, and no company paid for placement.</p></div></section>

